4.30.25  10:00 am   sure i can do something a lot for practice, but how do i know if i'm getting better? as opposed to just getting used to doing the thing while not getting better at it? for instance Alice does lifting but with bad form without realizing, and one day she injures herself because of it. or Bob does programming and writes code for years, but it's slow and unoptimized and he doesn't know because "it works fine on his end". These aren't great examples because it's hard to give a realistic example of me noticing what I'm doing wrong (since i can't notice it) but hopefully you see where i'm going with this

      you don't notice what you don't notice, but you're getting better anyway. Whether or not you're gonna have a clever breakthrough this week or next week, no need to worry about that either, you're still getting better without it, and a bonus breakthrough becomes only more likely as you continue
